parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat back bolt can cause the seat back to collapse or fall backwards, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The seat back does not stay up
flops backwards
does not stay vertical
the seat back collapses
the seat back falls into the rear seat
the seat back pushes forward when rear passengers push forward
the seat back does not lock into place upon impact.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of dealerships to properly repair recalled vehicles can lead to continued safety risks and potential accidents.
symptoms: The recall repair was not performed correctly
the dealership did not follow recall directives
the dealership did not schedule an appointment for recall repairs
the dealership did not call back to schedule an appointment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat adjustment mechanism can cause discomfort, distraction, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The driver's seat will not adjust
the seat back does not stay up
the seat back flops backwards.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injury or even death, as the driver and passengers are not adequately protected.
symptoms: The airbag does not deploy or deploys partially
the airbag light is illuminated
the airbag is torn or damaged
the airbag does not inflate fully.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag Malfunction due to Material Defect
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A material defect, such as a hole or tear in the airbag, can cause the airbag to malfunction or not deploy properly, leading to inadequate protection in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbag has a hole or tear
the airbag does not inflate fully
the airbag deploys partially.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the airbag warning light can indicate a problem with the airbag system, which may prevent the airbag from deploying properly in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the dealer claims it is not a problem
but the consumer is concerned about the safety of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the key to get stuck, making it difficult or impossible to turn the ignition on or off, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded. Additionally, the ignition switch failure can cause electrical shorts, leading to underdash wire harness fires, which can result in vehicle total loss.
symptoms: The key gets stuck in the ignition
the ignition switch stays in the ACC position
the key falls out while the vehicle is in motion
the ignition switch is difficult to turn
the starter won't work after the key is turned.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause electrical shorts, leading to underdash wire harness fires, which can result in vehicle total loss. Additionally, the electrical system failure can cause the brake lights and turn signals to malfunction, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The hazard warning lights do not work
the brake lights and turn signals do not function when the hazard warning lights are turned on
underdash wire harness fires occur.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause electrical shorts, leading to underhood fires, which can result in vehicle total loss.
symptoms: Underhood fires occur due to a short in the alternator.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle stalling can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially if it occurs at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls out while driving at any speed without prior warning.
